                <h1>The Evolution of Public Health: A Brief History</h1>
                <p>The history of public health traces back to ancient civilizations, where basic hygiene practices emerged to combat disease. In the 19th century, with the advent of germ theory, public health expanded significantly, focusing on sanitation and vaccination. Major reforms followed, leading to organized health agencies and global health initiatives, shaping today's public health systems.</p>
